• WE'VE GOT MORE FROM LOUISVILLE FROM THE ARCHERY TRADE ASSOCIATION EVENT.  (ATA)
  • We'll get you caught up on the latest and greatest archery products for 2016 with Craig Cushman from Hunters Specialties, Bryant Johnson from Real Avid and Matt Schillinger from AMS Bowfishing. 
  • Tina Chapman from Chapman's Resort and Guide Service on Mille Lacs has a fishing and ice conditions report.
  • And Greg Kaiser, Brian Peterson and Becca Clemens talk about plane crashes, SHOT Show and what weird things you can do in Las Vegas besides gambling.

Northland Outdoors General Manager Tim Bogenschutz explains how Northland Outdoors came together. And Jamie Dietman recaps his second elk trip of the year and offers tips that might help you plan a trip.

Jared Wiklund from Pheasants Forever will catch us up on how the pheasant season has been across the Northland. We’ll talk about December regulation changes and where you should look for roosters once the snow hits the ground.

Doug Leier from the North Dakota Game and Fish Department will recap the deer season in North Dakota and give us a preview of hard water fishing and give us some insight into the spearing regulations.

Jamie Dietman, Brainerd Lakes area guide gives his thoughts on muskie stocking across the region and new Red Lake winter regulations. And Brian Peterson gives us a glimpse into the world of fat bikes and just where you can take them when the northland is covered in snow.
Marc Bacigalupi From The MN DNR And Becca Clemens

Marc Bacigalupi – MN DNR – Gives the DNR perspective on muskie stocking that has gotten a lot of attention. View the video from a recent public meeting at www.northlandoutdoors.com. And Becca Clemens talks about the biggest outdoors stories from the northland.
Jessica Brooks Talks Taxidermy And Greg Kaiser Explains The Can Cooker
Jessica Brooks – Taxidermist with Wild Images in Motion talks about how and why she got into taxidermy and some of the most unique projects she’s worked on. And Greg Kaiser explains the Can Cooker.

Uldis Bierznick from the GCOLA (Gull Chain Of Lakes Association) talks about why area residents and property owners don’t want to see muskies stocked in their lakes.  GCOLA members were polled, with 72% in opposition to muskie stocking in the Gull Chain, 20% in favor and 8% undecided.  Uldis explains the why some are opposed and some are for it. (Part 1 of 2)
Uldis Bierznick from the GCOLA (Gull Chain Of Lakes Association) talks about why area residents and property owners don’t want to see muskies stocked in their lakes. (Part 2 of 2)

Scott Tedrick discusses plans for a new whitewater park in southwestern Minnesota. The Granite Falls municipal dam site has the potential to create a “chute” that can be used by whitewater rafters, tubers and other recreational users. Numerous species of fish can also benefit. Plus, updates from the Northland Outdoors staff: Brian Peterson talks about SNOW Fest. Greg Kaiser offers a great gift idea for the outdoorsman who is looking to do more ice fishing, and the top stories from the week at www.NorthlandOutdoors.com with Becca Clemens.

Jamie Dietman joins us to talk about using hot dogs for tip up fishing.  Plus, updates from the Northland Outdoors staff: Brian Peterson talks about First Day Hike Initiative.  Tim Bogenschutz tells the story about his favorite Christmas gift, and we’ll recap the top stories from our website.
LW Report, Wis. Deer Recap - Part 1

Joe Henry has an fishing and ice conditions report from Lake of the Woods. Kevin Wallenfang from the WI DNR recaps the Wisconsin Deer Season, explains the new private/public bonus tag system and also how the crossbow season is structured. (Part 1 of 2)
Kevin Wallenfang from the WI DNR recaps the Wisconsin Deer Season, explains the new private/public bonus tag system and also how the crossbow season is structured. (Part 2 of 2)
Jamie Dietman is back to talk ice fishing, ice conditions, Red Lake trips and more.

Darwin Sumner, guide from the Red Lake Reservation talks about this unique fishing destination. Bob St Pierre from Pheasants Forever/Quail Forever recaps the Pheasant and Grouse seasons for each state across the Northland. (Part 1 of 2)
Rooster/Ruffie Recap With Bob St Pierre - Part 2
Bob St Pierre from Pheasants Forever/Quail Forever recaps the Pheasant and Grouse seasons for each state across the Northland. (Part 2 of 2)
